&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Outpatient Supervisor - (Band 3)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Advert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to work at the Leeds Teaching Hospital as an Outpatient Supervisor for the Haematology Team supporting the patient administration team. We are looking for an ambitious individual to fill this post and who will play a key role in managing the patient administration teams and the patient pathway. Primarily the role will support the PSC team in all aspects of patient administration including data quality, staff management and our ability to deliver a streamlined patient pathway and quality patient experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be expected to communicate sensitively and effectively with members of the public as well as all levels of staff within the Haematology (Oncology CSU) including all clinical staff. The role of outpatient supervisor entails a variety of daily tasks to deliver and implement changes within their designated team. You will be providing a professional front line service interfacing with the NHS.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a very busy area and you will be expected to prioritise your own workload. The ability to work on your own initiative but at the same time as an integral part of a team is essential. Knowledge of patient administration procedures and protocols is essential. In addition, experience of National Access targets including waiting list management is desirable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must be flexible in their approach and have previous experience of service delivery against key performance targets. In return we offer a friendly, supportive and dedicated working environment. If you think you have the necessary skills and experience we would like to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information/informal discussion or visit please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gamuchirai Gore (PSC) on 01132068503 or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;gamuchirai.gore@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sue Yates (APSC) on 01132067774 or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;susan.yates11@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous Candidates Need Not To Apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
